Remarks:
Have been waking up to this bird for years now and still am unable to identify it. I call her "Singy Singy". She is usually the first bird to sing every morning around 5am. She sings for about 15 minutes until the rest of the birds start singing then she stops. Until recently I only used to hear her in the morning. But since the covid quarantine, I sometimes hear her for about 15 minutes right around sunset. Very curious to know what type of bird sings this beautiful song that brings me so much tranquility in the morning.
